data.title: Hall of Fame
data.meta_description: The official Hall of Fame for the Cornell University Big Red
data.text:
The Cornell Athletics Hall of Fame was initiated in 1978. It became a reality through the thoughtfulness and generosity of the late Ellis H. Robison '18, whose devotion, advice and financial support to his alma mater started as soon as he graduated from the university. Membership in the Hall will stand at 641 after the Class of 2022 induction.

In 2006, the Hall of Fame room moved into Friends Hall, where a high tech touch screen displayed features biographies and photos of every Hall of Famer. That display moved online in 2015 and can be found below.

Year-By-Year Induction Stories

The Big Red Athletics Hall of Fame honors the achievements of the college's outstanding individual student-athletes, coaches and supporters who have enhanced and reinforced the Universitys commitment to athletic excellence.

To nominate a worthy Cornellian for the Athletics Hall of Fame, please contact John Webster at jlw9@cornell.edu.

The web version of the Cornell Athletics Hall of Fame is due in large part to the hard work of Big Red student-athletes Sarah Wilfred '07 (track and field and Athletics Hall of Fame Class of 2017), Amanda Linnertz '08 (lacrosse) and Adam Agata '10.
